Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.util

Class UniqueMap<K extends Unique,V>

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.util.UniqueMap<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type of the key objects
V - the type of the value objects
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, Serializable, Iterable<V>
public class UniqueMap<K extends Unique,V> extends Object implements Iterable<V>, Serializable, Countable
A unique map uses Unique objects as keys and maps each key to a value. This map assumes the keys are all members of the same set of unique values, meaning their hash codes are unique sequential integers starting at 0.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • UniqueMap

      public UniqueMap(int capacity)
      Constructs a new unique map which starts with the capacity to store up to a given number of keys. Unique maps will expand as needed, but if the number of keys a map will hold is known in advance this can same some array allocation.
      Parameters:
      capacity - the number of keys to hold

    • put

      public void put(K key, V value)
      Maps a given unique key to a given value. The key object's hash code method should return a positive integer that is unique for all other keys in the same set. If the key given returns the same hash code as some other key object, the original mapping will be overwritten. The map will automatically expand to accommodate the mapping.
      Parameters:
      key - the unique key
      value - the value
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the key's hash code is less than 0
